---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import SoundEffectsComponent from '../../../../components/SoundEffects.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import AddComponentTabs from '../../../../components/AddComponentTabs.astro';

const copyableHtml = `<label class="settings__checkbox-label">
  <input type="checkbox" class="settings__checkbox" data-sound-effects aria-label="Play sound on click" />
  <span>Play sound on click</span>
</label>
<p class="settings__help-text">Short click sound when you interact with buttons and links. Off by default.</p>`;
---

<DocsLayout title="Sound Effects — Vanilla" description="Toggle for play sound on click with vanilla HTML + JS.">
  <section>
    <h2>Sound Effects</h2>
    <p>Checkbox that toggles “Play sound on click”. Persists in <code>localStorage</code> (key <code>soundEffects</code>). The actual click sound is played by a global script in the layout (see <a href="/docs/components/sound-effects">Astro doc</a>).</p>
    <AddComponentTabs componentName="Sound Effects" />
    <h3>Live example</h3>
    <p>The toggle below is a working example (same Astro component). Enable it and click any button or link on the page.</p>
    <div class="example">
      <div class="example-title">Live Example</div>
      <SoundEffectsComponent />
    </div>

    <h3>HTML</h3>
    <p>Copy the markup below. Wire the checkbox with a script that reads/writes <code>localStorage.soundEffects</code>. Include the layout sound script for the click sound to play.</p>
    <CodeBlock code={copyableHtml} language="html" />

    <p><a href="/docs/components/sound-effects">Astro Sound Effects</a> · <a href="/docs/svelte/components/sound-effects">Svelte</a></p>
    <p><a href="/docs/vanilla/components">← Back to Vanilla components</a></p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .example { margin: var(--spacing-6) 0; padding: var(--spacing-4); background: var(--background-alt); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); }
  .example-title { font-size: var(--font-size-sm); font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium); color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing-wider); }
</style>
